Hello,

I am working with Unity and C# and faced an issue with IEnumerator, loops and the "yield"-keyword. I created an endless loop in the following setup (example).

```
IEnumerator Foo()
{
    int number = 0;
    while(true)
    {
        if (number == 1)
        {
            yield return new WaitForSeconds(1.0f);
        }

// Missing a yield return outside if-block
    }
}
```

Considering the code above, "yield return new WaitForSeconds(1.0f);" will never be reached and therefore, an endless loop is created.
I would like to suggest that the compiler creates a warning or error when such a situation occurs similar to the following:

```
public bool IsThatTrue(bool b)
{
    if (b)
    {
        return b;
    }
}
```

In this case, the compiler tells me that not all code paths return a value.

I feel like it should be possible to recognize the potential endless loop (while(true)) and give a warning if inside that loop not all paths have a "yield return".

Kind regards
Kevin

